# StochasticPoolingRegionSelection

Stochastic Pooling Region Selection is a varient on the standard pooling layer intended to be another option researchers can use in their neural network architectures.

Kind of like a mix of:
  - Benjamin Graham's Fractional Max-Pooling: http://arxiv.org/abs/1412.6071
  - Zeiler & Fergus's Stochastic Pooling: http://arxiv.org/abs/1301.3557
